═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
SUPPLY CHAIN & VENDORS
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

PRIMARY 503A COMPOUNDING PHARMACY: FCC (Formulation Compounding
  Center, Lewisville TX). Fax-based ordering via the
  send-rx-fax edge function (Sinch fax service). Ships
  refrigerated direct to clinic or patient.

SECONDARY 503A: Empower Pharmacy (Houston, TX). Backup for
  FCC supply issues. Account in process.

LAB PARTNER: LabCorp via client billing. Account application
  in flight. 2-3 week approval. Critical path for launch.

E-PRESCRIBING: DrFirst Rcopia / iPrescribe for retail pharmacy
  Rx (FDA-approved transdermal HRT alternatives, ancillaries).
  EPCS upgrade for Schedule III is deferred — fax-to-FCC handles
  compounded TRT in Georgia (legally compliant for cash-pay).

MEDICAL-SURGICAL: Henry Schein.
SHARPS DISPOSAL: Stericycle.
PAYMENTS: Stripe (test → live mode transition needed pre-launch).
SMS: Twilio.
FAX: Sinch.
TELEHEALTH: Doxy.me.

VENDORS WE DO NOT USE (and why):
- Tailor Made Compounding — DOJ prosecution, $1.79M forfeiture
  for distributing unapproved peptides. Do not recommend or
  refer to in code.
- Verified RX / PATH Peptides — gray-market "physician-use only"
  branding. Not pharmacy-grade. Pending verification of their
  503B partner before any engagement.
- Any "research-grade" or "physician use only" peptide vendor
  not operating under 503A or 503B authority.

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
REGULATORY POSTURE
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

We are deliberately the "responsibly sourced" alternative in
the Augusta wellness market. This is a competitive moat AND a
liability shield. Code, copy, and protocols must reflect it.

PEPTIDES — Cat 2 LIST AS OF MAY 2026:
  NOT OFFERED (FDA prohibition on compounding):
    BPC-157 — replaced with Pentadeca Arginate (PDA), the
      regulatory-cleared successor with similar mechanism
    CJC-1295 / Ipamorelin — on Cat 2, FCC may pull anytime
    Thymosin Alpha-1 — on Cat 2
    Selank — on Cat 2
    GHK-Cu (injectable form only) — Cat 2; topical cream OK

  YELLOW LIGHT (verify with FCC before promoting):
    TB-500 (Thymosin Beta-4) — on Cat 2 but FCC currently
      compounds. Verify FCC's compliance position before
      featuring prominently. The Healing stack depends on this.

  GREEN LIGHT (clearly legal):
    PT-141 (Bremelanotide) — FDA-approved as Vyleesi
    Pentadeca Arginate (PDA) — not on Cat 2
    Sermorelin — not on Cat 2
    NAD+ — not on Cat 2 (any delivery method)

RETATRUTIDE — DO NOT OFFER. Not FDA-approved, FDA explicitly
  prohibits compounding under federal law, Eli Lilly patent
  protection. Multiple FDA warning letters issued Sept 2025
  to compounders selling it. We are building a "Retatrutide
  Early Access Registry" instead — email capture, day-one
  prescribing when approved (estimated 2027). Do not add
  retatrutide to any storefront menu.

KETAMINE — NOT OFFERED. Legacy artifact only.

HORMONE THERAPY:
  - Schedule III testosterone via FCC compounding (cash-pay,
    Georgia fax-Rx is legally compliant; no EPCS required)
  - Compounded transdermal HRT cream is the LEAD product
    (FDA-approved patches in nationwide shortage through 2026)
  - FDA-approved alternatives (gels, sprays, patches when
    available) prescribed via DrFirst Rcopia for patients who
    prefer them

GLP-1 COMPOUNDING:
  - Semaglutide and tirzepatide via FCC under 503A patient-
    specific authority. Legally compoundable under specific
    conditions. Watch for FDA shortage list status changes.

